SIMPLE: slipshod
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Slipshod
<hw>Slip"shod`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Wearing
shoes or slippers down at the heel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The shivering urchin bending as he goes,⟦br⟧
With <qex>slipshod</qex> heels.</q> <rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Figuratively: Careless in dress, manners, style,
etc.; slovenly; shuffling; <as>as, <ex>slipshod</ex> manners; a
<ex>slipshod</ex> or loose style of writing</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thy wit shall ne'er go <qex>slipshod</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slipshoe</ent>⟦br⟧
